        <section name="Examples">
            <div>
                <p>
                    RioSpan is, essentially, a thin wrapper around Infinispan allowing it to be deployed to
                    Rio. It
                    provides a lightweight core and some examples demonstrating its use. For details on RioSpan
                    internals and how they can be used in your applications see
                    <a href="./extending-riospan.html">Extending RioSpan</a>
                    .
                </p>
                <div id="infobox">
                    <img alt="Information Box Icon" src="images/information.gif" />
                    The examples require Rio to be built, installed, and started, and RioSpan to be built and
                    installed,
                    per the instructions on
                    <a href="./five-mins.html">RioSpan in 5 Minutes</a>
                    .
                </div>
                <p>The following examples are provided</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <a href="./hotrod.html">HotRod</a>
                        - Remote access to Infinispan caches using Infinispan's proprietary
                        client/server protocol
                    </li>
